name: Afternoon Run
description: Day 1 of 7 mile week

name: Week 1
description: 40 miles during the week of 5/22.

name: Evening Run
description: Oops. Probably too fast of a run. Also had a huge dump right after. 75 and sunny was part of why it was so fast tho

name: Evening Run
description: Damn Minnesota has some hills - 55 cloudy and windy, actually ran w a shirt

name: Call it 9 @ Battle Creek
description: Suuuuuper hilly. Still felt like I was going pretty hard so it probably was just sub 7 pace all things considered. Great weather, great trails on a bike. Would love to get back to mountain biking some time.

name: 7 miles lmao kids
description: Felt way better than I thought I would after crazy hills yesterday. Around mile 5 some kids tried to race me so that was about a 5:55. Still wasn't too tough though.

name: 7 miles, kinda hot and felt sore
description: Ran a while ago actually, felt pretty sore. Milk mile tomorrow so we'll see how that goes.

name: Milk mile and other stuff
description: 2 mi wu, 1 mi cd, milk mile in 6:20. Honestly way better than I expected, finished ad threw up immediately after crossing the line and felt better instantly. Got kicked down by a New Trier bub though...

name: 8 miles v hot
description: With sauce and Chris Brenk, was about 90 degrees. Also my back is hurting like crazy, some sort of muscle soreness.

name: 7:47 injury
description: Back is doing somewhat better, but my left hip is ridiculously tight. I can walk without falling over now but running is really painful and slow. Don't have any work obligations the next two days so my only plans are to keep my leg iced, run 1 mile and head to the doc tomorrow. At least this isn't during height mileage.

name: 1 mile 7:33
description: Almost forgot to post. Didn't do too much today, pretty bummed I wasn't able to do a long run or something. Hip is improving, just not fast enough. Maybe I can work on my glamour muscles in the mean time.

name: 1 mile, about 50 percent better
description: Actually took the slightest bit of aerobic effort today. Hip is notably better but definitely still needs to improve more. Should be fully better by Saturday or Sunday. Also did an hour bike ride this morning.
Hip actually felt way better walking around today. Pretty damn frustrating, feel like a caged dog. Can't wait to get back on the roads soon.

name: Afternoon Ride
description: Somewhere between 26 and 27 miles. Hip felt way better, back hurting just a little bit but at least that's symmetrical pain. Going to run later when my quads stop killing me

name: Last day of 1
description: Probably not the greatest idea, but ramping it up a little felt easier on my hip. Quads are pretty sore, but hip is at about 80%. Plan to mix up biking and running tomorrow.

name: Afternoon Ride
description: 90 degrees and sunny, also weirdly windy.

name: Night Run
description: Hip really started to tighten up a little after a mile. Going into the trainer in a couple days, can't wait for that
Still super tight. Can't life my knees up without causing a lot of pain. Going to see the trainer on Tuesday, if anyone can fix my hip this trainer is probably it
Felt better, still not improving nearly fast enough.

Felt okay, also hammered a few miles on the bike so my quads are pretty fried. Trainer is in Thursday. I'm getting the feeling that this is fate's way of making me take time off whether I like it or not.

Pain level has pretty much stagnated. Going to the trainer soon. Whether I'm going 9 minus pace or 5 minute pace, my leg hurts the same, only difference is the aerobic value I get from what little running I am doing.

name: Morning Ride
description: The total time included stops. Did 7 with my dad at about 14-15mph. Then did about 12 alone at about 17mph and then did 3 with my mom at about 10-11mph. Not sure I'm even counting that last part lol.

name: Afternoon Run
description: Hip felt way better, back felt somewhat worse. Also did 2 hours of yardwork in 85 degrees and 60% humidity. Ready to spend the rest of the day indoors.
Went to the PT place today, already feeling somewhat better and have a number of exercises to do. In four years of running every day I've honestly never wanted to run a real distance so much.

name: 4 25:53 we back
description: Finally back at it. Felt decent, still painful but not quite bad enough to keep me from running. Asian kids wearing dank tees is now a thing.

Felt pretty great to get a real run in finally. Back felt much improved today, hammys were slightly better, but not imbalanced in terms of pain anymore. Overall felt much better than even yesterday. That being said, I'd still get my ass kicked into another dimension if I tried to race right now.

name: Evening Run
description: On the dprt. The moment you cross over from Lake County to Cook County (where Chicago is) the trail turns into a complete mess. WOAT county in the US. Anyway, was a decent run, last mile was about 6:05, felt more like a 5:40 close but that's what returning from injury is like.
Still improving every day. Closed sub 6, looking forward to continual improvement

Forest preserve, windy but still 90 degrees so my calves were feeling pretty tight. Hammys were about the same and back is basically better. Also had some arch pain, so I guess it's time for new kicks
Arch pain still present, calves and hammys felt better while back pain was slightly worse. Overall improved, arch pain was less noticeable when I picked up the pace a bit strangely

name: 10 LR 67:56
description: Didn't feel great, legs kinda ran out of gas part way thru. Planning to do 65-70 next week
Felt a lot better than yesterday. Had a lot more energy in my legs, also was nice to run in sunny and 75 degrees.

Finally had a day where I was feeling good. Did an impromptu fartlek on mile 8 of 2mins at run pace and 30secs try not to poop recovery. Got to the bathroom and it was kind of like the end of my milk mile, but the last 2 were at a comfortable 6:00 pace.
Finally back to consistently feeling good. Still plan to have the 4th run be my first workout/race since conference. Should be something to see.

name: 8 thru satan forest
description: Only ran through it for a mile, but the single track was super rough and muddy. Otherwise probably could have gone without the 6:10 pace but I wasn't pushing much either.

name: Humid 13 LR
description: 13 miles in 80 degrees and 70% humidity. Probably not the best idea to do my longest run in 8 or 9 months on such a hot humid day, but I did anyway. Also around mile 8 a tunnel was a few feet submerged under water so I had to climb across a fence. Pretty sketchy.

name: 6.4 as humid but hotter
description: Still super humid but 5-10 degrees warmer. Really not looking forward to running again tonight. Like really really don't want to.
Felt super tired earlier today, wasn't even sure I'd be able to run today. 58:23 is also Tadese's WR half. 10k on Tuesday.
Felt a lot better. Was cruising around 6:00 pace for a few middle miles. 65 for the week in singles

name: Pre race lol
description: Had some IT band pain as well as arch pain. Hoping to feel better for the 10.3k in the morning.

name: 10k race disaster
description: 1.5 WU. First couple miles felt hard but doable. Dropped out at 4.5 with bad arch pain, talked to the chiropractor after. V frustrating but also good I didn't injure myself today. Time to reevaluate my training, I think I've been trying to get back into it too quickly.

name: 3.3 super arch trouble
description: Felt great thru 2 miles, but my left IT and arch started hurting a lot. On the bright side, I couldn't walk yesterday due to a blister, but that's all better. Plan to hang around 40-50 miles per week until I'm fully healthy. Priority is health and then mileage. Still 4+ months to nats.

name: Arch still hurts
description: Felt basically fine for the first 2. Around then I felt my left arch and IT flare up again and by 3 it wasn't worth continuing. The last 3 days whether I go fast or slow everything starts hurting at 2m and hurts a lot at 3m, so I figured I'd at least get a speed benefit today because I wasn't getting a distance benefit. Seeing trainer again soon. Haven't had any injuries for a while so I guess it's about time for me :/. Hopefully this means I'll be healthy all next year though.

name: Arches still hurting
description: Felt somewhat better, didn't want to push it too much though.

name: Hammer bike ride
description: Supplementary bike ride. Legs v tired afterwards

name: Everything feeling better
description: Definetely still felt twinges in my arches and left IT, but felt night and day better than the last 3 days in general. 8 tomorrow would make 35, I'll probably do 50 next week with a workout. I'm hoping to get my mileage to 90 by the end of the summer, but my aggregate mileage won't be so high. Better to do fewer, quality, injury-free miles than to jump foolishly back into high mileage again.

name: Pretty sore :/
description: Went to the gym with a couple friends, super sore from that and my legs just felt gassed. Plan to do about 50-55 w a workout this coming week.

name: Crazy thunderstorm run
description: Constant lightning going the whole time. Forts two in 13:11 and last two in 12:11. Felt okay the first two and kinda bad the next two, had some cramping in my right arch this time, but it cleared up for the last 4. Also did the whole run as 1 mile loops around my neighborhood.

name: Post apocalyptic-flood run
description: Got going a bit for a couple bits, but I was generally able to hit 6:25-6:30 without breathing heavily at all. Enormous storm this morning, basement flooded, road flooded everywhere, so the humidity was off the chain. Sweatiest I've been in a while.

name: Should I w/out this week or not?
description: 6:10 pace felt pretty easy for most of it. Right arch was hurting for about 10 mins from 2.5 to 4 miles, so that would be an argument not to workout. On the other hand, I'm way behind on workouts and am feeling good besides my right arch.

name: Forgot to post for Monday
description: Forgot to post this before. Time is approximate.

name: Half mile tempo, need new flats
description: Most of the run was right at 7:00 pace. Was planning to do a 2 mile tempo, but my flats didn't feel great, probably had something to do with my bad 10k. My arch and IT were hurting before the 10k too, I think the flats just aggravated it. Wound up doing a half mile in 2:13. Probably too fast but I felt good, especially aerobically. Will do some sort of wout next week

name: 5.5 and then 2x400 in new streaks
description: 5.5 in 34:58, like 6:22 pace. Calves felt a little tight but otherwise felt good especially once I got going. Got new Streak 6s today, ripped a couple of 400s in 63 and 60 in them, felt fast but I felt like I was only going like 67 pace. Maybe I have some track speed left after all.

name: Post hike LR
description: Felt pretty good, aside from the typical long run pains, looking forward to 60 next week.

name: Afternoon hike in Wisconsin
description: Went up to Kettle Moraine North with a couple friends. Nice day to go for a hike though.

name: Sore 6
description: Felt p sore, no real sharp pains though, just soreness that will fell better in a day or two. Plan to do a double and a w out this week.

name: Slow prog run
description: Felt decent at the start, got into feeling good and picked it up. Went from 6:34 down to 5:57,  probably doubling tomorrow.

name: Crazy storm run
description: Just as I was leaving it started pouring rain. Between the weather and some painful stomach problems I cut it from 8 to 5, but otherwise felt solid. Grats to the boys at Torchlight.

name: Northbrook Night LR
description: Felt pretty solid. Slowly picked up from 6:35 to 6:20 w/out feeling like pushing. Am looking forward to running in daylight tho

name: Huge storm night run
description: Pouring rain the whole time. Reasonably quick pace, especially given heavy shoes and shirt. Felt pretty easy though. Double and a workout to do this weekend.

name: Super humid WU
description: Felt more like 6:30 effort than 6:50. Didn't bode well for the workout. One of the humidest days so far this year.

name: 30sec workout
description: Did 26 30sec bursts. Felt pretty solid actually. Previous years this workout averaged about 6:05-6:10, so 5:50 average is well improved. Good to see that even with all that injury crap I'm still in much better shape than last summer.

name: Cool down with maximum chafing
description: Pretty quick for a cool down but wasn't really pushing. I think that shows that my workout didn't tax me all that much, which this workout really shouldn't.

name: Afternoon Run
description: Unbelievably humid out, ran on the indoor track nearby. Didn't feel great on my arch, so I cut it from 8 to 6. Doing the remaining six in a couple hours.

name: Night Run, p sore
description: Way less humid and cooler, still felt sore and was super tired. Got through 60 this week tho.

name: City bike with Dad
description: All approximate, nice and slow. Checked out a new trail in the city with my dad. Tire popped 3 miles away from the car on the way back. Currently waiting for him to pick me up :/

name: Sore again and now sick
description: Woke up with a bad headache, didn't feel it much of the day but was having trouble balancing on the run. Also calves were somehow even more sore than yesterday. I figure if I ran 25:35 at nats last year without working out 6 and 7 weeks out then an easy day in July won't make a difference. Mileage this summer is secondary to staying healthy. I'm already definitely in way better shape than last year, so I'm not too worried about keeping my mileage up as long as I'm always as healthy as I can be.

name: 13 hour work day and 13 mile LR
description: Felt a lot better than yesterday, still not great. Decided to turn it into my LR anyway. Pretty sure that was just dehydration. Another long day tomorrow and then relaxing on Thursday.

name: 9 miles kinda quick
description: Very humid, felt a little sore but otherwise pretty good.

name: Warm up
description: Felt okay, feeling pretty tired though.

name: 60s workout
description: Felt pretty solid. Did 12 of them and then did a 66 400 at the end. Averaged a little under 5 minute pace on the fast intervals.

name: 2.4 cool down
description: Started off kinda quick. Didn't feel great but when do cool downs feel good anyway.

name: Pretty fast 9 miles
description: Felt pretty solid. Did a 2:56 uphill after 2 miles and slowed it down to 6:15. 65 degrees felt awesome.

name: Started at 11:59, counts as a morning run
description: Felt pretty sore, super nice day though. Good to have my run done this early for a change.

name: First run of the day
description: Honestly thought I was going 6:30-6:40. In terms of aerobic ability I'm in about my best shape ever. However my legs have been super sore. I'm thinking about just doing a mile tomorrow and then doing 55 over the next 6 days. Definetely doing a cut back week either way.

name: Slow bike with parents
description: Nice and slow along the Prairie path with my parents. 80 degrees and shady so it was super nice.

name: Second run of the day
description: Felt better, I'm planning on just doing 1 tomorrow. Should be nice to have fresh legs on Tuesday.

name: 1 mile recovery
description: Definitely didn't feel great, glad I took an off day. 55 miles planned for the next 6 days.

name: 7 miles with the DFDC boys
description: First run over 7 of the summer. With Alex and Ben, good to finally run with then again. DPRT was super nice at night as always.

name: Cut back week LR
description: So bored that I ran on streets in Deerfield alphabetically. All on pavement, thought my IT was going to be a problem by mile 3 and 4 but it got better as I went along. Should try to hit slower paces but low 6:20s is feeling very natural in the last few weeks.

name: Easy run super humid
description: Very humid, didn't feel great. Hope to feel good enough to w out tomorrow. I might be able to win the alumni run this year which would be super sick

name: 60 degs and windy
description: Definitely felt a little heavy-legged at the start but got going and felt good. At the start I was cold outside for the first time in months.

name: 4x400 in flats (counts as wout)
description: 64.3 62.7 63.8 60.2. In my flats, felt really solid actually. Pushing a bit but I wasn't going so hard as to risk anything health-wise. Figured some shorter faster stuff would be more beneficial since my legs have been really heavy this week. Also counts as this weeks workout.

name: Short cool down
description: Yup

name: 8 mile PR lol
description: Felt super good. 65 degrees, 9:23 thru 1.5, so the last 6.5 were pretty evenly at 5:45 pace. Definetely felt like I was pushing a bit but still felt very controlled. Even though Gatlin isn't the greatest guy to win it it was still pretty awesome that the US went 1-2.

name: 6 miles with hs boys
description: Started off at like 7:00 pace and closed in 6:06 alone. Felt okay considering it was actually a morning run for once.

name: 7, crazy start to vacation
description: Ran back home from a concert at Ravinia to meet back with my family to leave on vacation. Turned on the car to leave and the battery died. Tried to jump it but it was totally dead. My dad and I found a battery half an hour away so we got it and are now on the road. On to Michigan.

name: 7.2 Petosky Michigan - lots of poop
description: Super nice run, pretty mad at my bowels though. Also felt sore and tired from car ride all day.

name: Canada - the USA with way more cigs
description: Felt really solid, both running-wise and bowel-wise. Ran around a couple islands on the St. Marie river in Sault Ste Marie, Ontario. So many people out walking while puffing darts. Pretty sick but also pretty smelly.

name: Run in Grand Marais (Michigan, sorry Chemlik)
description: Felt good, found some super cool single track stuff too treacherous to run on so I walked it for a bit.

name: Last run in the UP
description: Ran around a state park, mostly trails but a few roads mixed in. The park was there for an abandoned 1860s iron processing town on the coast, so there were some old buildings to run around. Sketchy trails in other places though. Got to our hotel and I'm 85% sure it's haunted.

name: Actual last run in yooper country
description: In Escanaba MI along the shoreline. Felt pretty sore but I think it was mostly due to it being the morning. Didn't push it at all, have the alumni run tomorrow. Supposedly Alex G isn't running so I'm going for the win. Plan to tuck in for the first mile and let loose on the second.

name: Alumni run WU
description: Felt pretty rough tbh.

name: Alumni run win and sub 10 for the 1st time
description: Ran 9:59.3, split 5:06.4 and then made a move and closed in 4:52.9. Obviously didn't feel awful but I've been having some gastrointestinal issues so I felt pretty queasy the second mile when I started racing harder. As a team the current guys won for the first time in 5 years so that wasn't great, so that was too bad, but taking the W and breaking 10 in the same race was pretty fun. Alex Gold or Jeff Bailey have always won this race since 2000, so this is the first time the trophy is leaving their houses this century, so that's also pretty cool. Will post a pic of the trophy soon.

name: Nice and slow cd
description: With some older alums. Fun to catch up with the boys.

name: B-day LR
description: Started off about 6:40 pace and wound up dropping the pace to the typical 6:20-6:25. Felt nice and easy the rest of it, though I did pick it up into the 6:10s for the last few miles. Ran thru the Botanic Gardens which were super nice today.

name: Quick but easy
description: Obviously felt a little quick but still definetely controlled. Out and back, 27:30 there and 26:45 back.

name: DPRT p fast, p easy
description: Ran over to the DPRT, down it about 2 miles and down a road connection I've never been on. First and last mile splits were 6:04. Felt fast but not forced at all.

name: Rainy and sore
description: Rainstorm started around 3 miles. Second day in new shoes but started feeling a little calf pain. Nothing too surprisingly painful, but still didn't feel great.

name: Don't eat KFC before a run
description:
Ate KFC at like 1pm but still felt it and had to make a pit stop. Also had some pretty bad congestion and felt super tired too, so overall felt pretty bad, not very sore tho. 

Got some sweet new headlights you tie into your shoelaces for my bday, so I don't have to carry a light anymore. That's actually super cool.

name: Earliest run alone all summer
description: Felt pretty sore, not horrible though. Had to make another port o potty stop.

name: Second run
description: Felt much better. Might run tomorrow not ing or evening, but 15-16 LR is Sunday night. All weekend is LOTR @ Ravinia so we have some weird ass hobbit food at the buffet to celebrate.

name: New doggo
description: Felt alright, LR tomorrow. Parents got home after my run with our new puppy, so now we have two dogs in the house. Should be an interesting next week.

name: Long and fast night LR
description: Ran a roundabout way to Palatine HS, partly because I was running through parks and k got put half a mile out of my way once. Dad was there to pick me up. Overall fun run.

name: gold bond      i nurture my skin     foot powder spraaaaaay
description: Felt pretty solid. Its kinda nice to have been doing these medium length runs at 6:00 pace or just over as I have been for the last few weeks. Haven't been doing many workouts but I have been running way faster than even last summer. Last week was 81 miles at 6:17 average.

name: 1 mile so basically off day
description: Plan to make this a 70 mile week with this 1 mile day. Definetely felt pretty sore on that mile because of a number of things, nothing too serious but definitely glad I took this day. Doing a bunch of stretching now, double tomorrow.

name: High School pre-meet
description: First day of school for the yungins, apparently there are 63 guys on the team so holy shit. There were about 40 when I was a senior. Ankle a little sore, did the last 4 alone and at like 6:15-6:20 pace.

name: Second run
description: Ankle still felt a little off, but overall felt good. Also it was only like 65 degrees. HSers have a meet tomorrow so that'll be fun.

name: Sore ankle
description: Ran during the HS meet, felt decent but tried doing a couple later on and my ankle was feeling really off. Might do some more later tonight but probably not. Ice and hopefully long run tomorrow

name: Last LR in Illinois
description: First 6 with Shore at about 6:35-6:40, alone last 9 at 6:20-6:25. Felt my ankle just a bit but icing it yesterday helped a lot. Obviously had some long run soreness the last couple and some pretty decent chafing, but felt nice and easy and went by relatively quickly. Always feels good to get the LR out of the way.

name: 4 years of running every day - WU
description: WU for hills. Also today is my 4 year anniversary of running every day, 1461 days.

name: 8 hills
description: 6 of the hills with Gold, last two with Shore. Can't exactly say that up the hills felt good, esp since my last time doing hills was in hs, but definitely good to get in.

name: CD - last time running with HSers
description: Super slow CD with the guys, ran thru downtown HP and screamed the Deerfield fight song. Classic.

name: Pre camp starts tomorrow
description: Started off slow and picked it up to about 6:00 pace. Felt v sore from hills.

name: Back with the BigO
description: We back. Felt not great but it was pretty early. Picked it up as it went on.

name: 2nd run
description: Nice

name: First morning run
description: With some boys, closed last mile with PT in around 6:05 feeling good.

name: 2nd run
description: âœ…

name: WU
description: Felt kinda sore, not a great prep for the w/out.

name: W/out
description: Ran about 16:02 thru the 3 mile with Keith and Butters, got a bad side stitch around 3.5 and had to stop, but most of the other guys wound up stopping at 4 anyway. Obviously too bad not to finish but feeling good at 16 minutes for 3 was good news for the rest of the season.

name: 4 sore CD
description: Sore with Turtle. Woat.

name: Morning 10
description: Felt okay at the start, although way better than I thought I'd feel. Felt good to get going a bit by the end.

name: 2nd run
description: With PT, felt pretty decent.

name: WOAT run
description: Got like 3-4 hours of sleep last night, felt and still feeling really sick. Tomorrow's going to be a 1 mile day unless I feel a lot better. Probably at least 60 secs per mile faster in terms of effort. Breathing was really hard.

name: Hard mile
description: Was laboring a lot, am not really able to take in enough air. Can't wait to get back to running.

name: Ughhh
description: Not fun

name: 6 miles fast and easy
description: Split 17:16 out and 16:37 back. Felt pretty easy, pushed it somewhat on the way back. Looking forward to GrindFest in 2 days. 25 laps is the goal.

name: Short pre-meet
description: GrindFest tomorrow. Got new pegs, arches still felt sore but heel felt better. Ian LaMere - I'm coming for you...

name: 1.2 WU
description: WU for Grind Fest

name: Grind Fest 17th place
description: 17th place overall, 30 laps. Goal was 25 laps, so pretty happy overall. Also got a Christmas snowman for being top 20. 2nd U21 runner their, some sub-25 guy from Stevens Point beat me by like 2 laps.

name: The Yukon Boys - Loud and Proud
description: The Yukon Boys search for gold, the Yukon Boys they're not too old. The Yukon Boys they're not too young, the Yukon Boys they'll have some fun!

name: 50 mile week w/ lots of arch problems
description: Day by day: 6 4 8 11 9 3 9. Got new shoes for Christmas and took a few days to break them in, arches were very sore on Mon Tue and Sat, would have been 60-65 w/out those days. Tried to do workouts at the rec center but running on that track aggravated my arches even more. Yesterdays run progressed from 6:30 down to 5:45 through snow, which was the closest I got to a workout. Argentina here we come.

name: 10 on treadmill: 85 degrees is hot
description: Actually at mostly 4:06/km cause we're in BA now. Treadmill was inside but w/out AC so it was still 85 degrees. Cramped up some but not nearly as much as I could have considering it was so hot and I was on planes an in airports for 24 hours.

name: 95 degrees... classic January
description: Super hot outside, should cool off in the next couple of days. No workouts this week, getting acclimated to the temperature is hard enough.

name: 75 degrees felt pretty cool
description: Ran along a bunch of beautiful paths through parks on the north coast. Best run so far (only good run so far).

name: Fast I guess
description: Out and back along the day 1 route. Felt pretty good so decided to pick it up some. Short and slow tomorrow.

name: Hangover mile
description: Hangover mile, felt v bad and was like 10 or 15 below 0.

name: Pre-flight run
description: Last run in the cold. Felt pretty decent, could have and should have run longer but didn't have the time too. Nest 5 days will be at 60mpw pace.

name: Hot and sore
description: Had a long bus ride, plus it was 90 degrees. Plan to get 60 in this week.

name: WU
description: Warm up for tempo.

name: Treadmill Tempo
description: On the treadmill, so not quite as hard as outside, but still really happy I was able to run that in 80-85 degrees. Felt pretty easy, did the first 1.5 in 7:50 and the last 0.9 at 3:00/k (4:48/m). Felt fast but controlled. Might do some 400s or something later this week.

name: CD
description: Done

name: 7 tread
description: Won the workout room. Was good.

name: Tread LR in 32 degrees
description: That's celsius, so about 90 degrees. 97 degrees in the sun tho. 1st mile 7:30, 2-10 in 7:00, 11 in 6:30 and 12 in 5:45 closing in 75 for the last quarter. Super hot but its done.

name: Tread again
description: Ya

name: Peanut allergy aftermath
description: Ate some snacks that apparently had peanut paste (peanut is mani instead of cacahuate here in Argentina apparently), so started getting covered in hives and made myself puke. Wound up going to the hospital with prof and got a corticosteroid shot. Not sure that it did much of anything, though. Waited as long as I could before getting my run in so as to not reaggravate my reaction. Run hurt a lot as my body was just exhausted from the reaction.

name: Fast but tough
description: Dropped the hammer a little more than I should have, especially since I was still super tired from yesterday. Not going to be able to make it 60 cause of yesterday but still should be able to get well into the 50s.

name: Evening Run
description: Still pretty sore, ran through some of the slums of Santa Fe, but it was still light so I felt pretty safe. Without Friday this would have been well over 60 miles this week. Overall my fitness right now isn't great but should be back on track in a couple days. Really looking forward to coming back in a couple weeks and tearing it up at the Showcase.

name: 10 p fast
description: Felt pretty decent, calf started tightening up around mile 6. The hotel here in Santa Fe has pretty bad beds so that's probably why. Switching to a less shitty bed tonight, hopefully calf is loosened up by tomorrow. Also found a track both here and in San Justo, hope to get at least one w out in this week on one of them.

name: 90 and sunny
description: Was v hot. Ran on some nice paths, wish I could have run a little later tho.

name: 2 short tempos
description: Two tempos: one for only about 0.9 but I hammered too much, like 4:45-4:50 pace. Closed in a 1.5 tempo in 7:48, or 5:12 pace. Second one felt better. Was having some pain in my left calf and lower achilles, so need to watch that. Overall pleasantly surprised that I got the second tempo in as easy as it was.

name: We out here more than ever before
description: 90 and very sunny. Had to make a few stops in the shade to avert heat stroke. Ran through corn fields here in San Justo, Santa Fe, AR, far and away the most obscure place I've ever been. Town's actually super sick tho.

name: Thru the streets of San Justo
description: San Justo's actually a sick town. About 30,000 people, so just big enough where I can run around the town without getting bored. Was only about 85 since the sun was setting, so much nicer.

name: WU
description: Yup. Found a dirt track on the east side if San Justo. Should be good for a workout. Also some random family came up to me, sat down while I was tying my shoes and we talked for a while about what our group has been doing. This town is seriously pretty sick. Too bad we have to leave tomorrow morning.

name: Workout - crappy track 8x300
description: Worst quality track I've ever seen but better than nothing. Its really dry here so most of the track was literal piles of sand, much harder to run on than even the poorly kept up dirt roads. Still ran 48 for the first 6 and 47 for the last two. Felt decent, probably was more like 45-46 effort throughout if not faster because of the terrain. Was hoping to do an actual scripted workout but lane 1 in the home straight was really deteriorated. Was vvvvv tired afterwards, but pretty excited I was able to run close to mile pace given such difficult conditions.

name: CD
description:
CD through the town of San Justo. Picked it up a bit the last couple of miles so the average pace was pretty fast. 

The following section will simply be a diary of one of the greatest nights of my life. 

Written starting at 7:21 am on a bus leaving San Justo for Mendoza (at least 13 hours of a bus ride away) (also still drunk and without having slept for about 25 hours). 

So basically we went to a restaurant downtown for pizza (argentine pizza, kinda weird and not the greatest but ill take what I can get) and lisos (8.5 ounce glasses of unpasteurized argentine beer - delicious).  Meal was solid, brought a pretty hefty amount of crap vodka with me and chased it with free pops. After that me, Christian Beck and Mike Perry contacted an accordionist that we saw perform the night before to find out what the party scene was like in San Justo.

After a while we met up with him and started walking to the apartment of some guy who he sang with in another group (who we met the night before. He looked just like an Argentine Mel Gibson, so literally only knew him as Mel even though hid name was something starting with a c). Turned out his day job was as a motorcycle mechanic, and his apartment was the second floor of his shop right along the main highway through town. Also btw this guy was 60 years old.

So the four of us had picked up 4 liters of beer on our way there, and he had a table and benches out front where the five of us sat for 2 hours or so. The four of us yungins (the accordionist was only 19) drank 5 liters of beer over that time, just guys bein dudes talking about girls, trucks and what we liked about San Justo. 

After a while Mel said he would take us in his truck to the north part of town where the party was happening. We got in the van and endured some sketchy argentine driving for a few minutes before getting to the club at about 2:30. At this point the party was just starting. We said goodbye to Mel, and just when we got there like 10 other Oles showed up that had been walking around for a while. 

Me and Noah Johnson started boolin with some 30 year old dudes for a while and payed the cover fee. Next part was just a 2 hour blur. I got some super good fruit drink from the bar of the club (it was entirely outside) and left the group of oles entirely. Found a couple groups of Argentine dudes and a group of Argentine girls over the next couple hours, talked and exchanged social media.  Long story short, we left the club-thing at about 5:30 and headed back to the hotel. 

The bus was leaving at 7:00 so I had a perfect ninety minutes to pack up. Now it's 7:40 and I'm chilling on the bus after the hotel breakfast, still feeling pretty drunk and ready for the bus ride. One of the greatest nights of my life. Good night you stupid runners.

name: Mendoza night run
description: Seems like there's some pretty good nightlife here. Felt pretty damn sore after a 14 hour bus ride.

name: run
description: ran

name: Decided that this should be a cut back week
description: Decided that this is gonna be a cut back week since I've been hitting the mileage pretty hard the last 3-4 weeks. Still plan to go for 45-50. Feel like kind of a lazy bitch tho.

name: Pre tempo run
description: Had to take a massive shit once I got to downtown Vista Flores, so had to walk a mile out of town to some bushes. Was woat.

name: Hammer tempo
description: From town along a bike path back go the hotel. Felt fast but def controlled, splits were like 4:57 to 5:06. Also had to deal with some pretty uneven paths in town, probably slowed me down a little bit. Overall was a really good confidence builder, hope to run under 8:40 at the opener depending on how the competition is.

name: LR with many scary doggos
description: Felt alright, a little tight because of the tempo yesterday. Running through streets near Vista Flores, near where we're staying, but also around some 9 square block town called Los Sauces which is pretty sick. Pic below. Also had 2am incredible view of the Andes. Later on found a couple packs of dogs who I just let come up to me since I couldn't outrun them, they could have torn me apart if they wanted to. One pair lookedike complete wild dingos. Was vvvv scary. Next run will be one of my craziest ever.

name: Drunk 1 am run through Argentine vineyards
description: Yeah, so I did that. Still pretty drunk rn. Have a bus to catch in less than 6 hours, bus ride will be at least 15 hours so I wasn't sure I would have enough time to get the mile in after going to sleep. Hopefully ill have some time to get another 4-5 in on the treadmill tomorrow night but no guarantees. P.S. today is day 1614, almost 4.5 years of running every day. Doot doot folks.

name: Back to the Atlantic side and its v humid
description: Technically Mendoza was a desert in terms of its yearly rainfall, plus its more humid than usual back here in BA so I turned into a liquid. Felt alright otherwise though

name: 8 miles fastish
description: Felt pretty good throughout. One thing I have been noticing is that my Achilles are hurting for the first mile or so, but that goes away pretty quick. Do have a couple of things to talk with Colton with when I get back but nothing that severe. Need to do more proper workouts though.

name: Almost 7 fasterish
description: Picked it up over the course of the run; last 3 were under 17 mins. Felt really good actually, going to count this as a long tempo, hope to get a track workout in later this week.

name: EZ 7
description: On the treadmill at 4:09/k. Was good.

name: Accidental long run, very haut
description: Earliest run in weeks so that I could make it to the huge forest preserve downtown that closes at three. Everybody in this country runs at 7pm so that makes no sense. Was nice but I got lost and wound up doing my long run in 90 degs and sun. Ouch burn.

name: 31st and final run in Argentina
description: On the treadmill, felt easy. Treadmill had internet connection so I could watch some dank races while running, plus it was hot out. Doot doot Argentina.

name: Memorial Joe Coffey run
description: First day running in Santiago Chile. Calling this the Joe Coffey memorial not because it was fast but because I ran out of clean running clothes and smelled like a rotting animal carcass. Like literally gagged from the smell when I put it on. Maybe this will help me get All-American this track season though.

name: Earliest run since LaCrosse XC meet
description: Found a nice bike path along the crappy river that runs through Santiago. It's a major river but it looks more like a drainage ditch.  Recorded a couple ks at 3:50-3:55 so it was probably a longer run than it says.

name: Last run in this hemisphere
description: Holy cow time to go back home, its crazy. Run was good, was stiff guy at the start but I picked it up down to 6min pace by the end. See y'all in the states

name: Easy 8 upstairs
description: With Sauce and later Cathy. Middle miles were all around 6:30, felt easy. Short workout tomorrow.

name: First track workout back
description: WU was too fast on the second mile with PT. Workout was short and easy but felt really good. Cool down easy. Looking forward to the race Friday, just going to have some fun with it.

name: Premeet
description: 3k tomorrow yeet

name: First race WU
description: EZPZ. 3k here we come.

name: Season debut 3k
description: Great to be back. Race went out in like 5:52 and I closed in 2:52. Happy overall, but I definetely could have gone faster with more race experience and speed workouts. Made a pretty dumb and funny move with 600 to go and realized I couldn't really hold that pace alone but I still held on for the win pretty safely. Good debut overall.

name: Post-race tempo
description: Nice and easy on the treadmill, good day of work overall. 4 miles in sub-20 between this and the race lol

name: CD
description: Time to watch this meet for literally 6 more hours

name: Cold run with Nobs+Pael
description: Jeff tmrw

name: Ouch oof ow my knee
description: Runners knee, rip. Was going to do Jefferson but did short Bryce instead and walked a bunch of it. Will go into trainer tmrw and ice and such. Workout not till wednesday, and then race sat. Here we go.

name: Into the Rockies
description: 5 uphill didnt feel too bad, 5 downhill felt effortless. Beautiful place to run.

name: Easy shakeout
description: Saw Emma Coburn and Will Leer, was sick. Snowy but looking like it should melt off by afternoon wout.

name: Lots of 2s
description: Felt good, not crazy fast but we're also at high alt

name: CD
description: Holy slow. Sick

name: Butter tastes good but not good for a run
description: Put butter on a lot of foods last night, had to stop a few times on the run. Ran into this Irish runner here for training and ran with him for a couple miles. Also ran past Saarel and some other Buffs. Would have been a great run if not for the GI distress.

name: Back in the Field of Deer
description: Pushed a little too hard, felt pretty good but not actually so sure that the alt training made a difference, even first day back. Alaska run tomorrow.

name: Workout
description: Workout was pretty good. Ran it at West Anchorage HS, tons of snow on the ground but it was warm so the track was covered with ice and puddles. Ran all the way in lane 9 and mostly avoided all the crap. Did make lines a little confusing. 600m in 1:39, went out way too hard and fell off the back half. 300s were 47 up to 49 and the 200s were 31 down to 28. Felt hard but overall decent workout, esp with wind and trainers, not to mention a ton of traveling the last 2 days.

name: 9 around Anchorage
description: Super nice day, warmer than Deerfield or Northfield lol. Found a super nice but icy trail so those miles were way slower. Otherwise fairly fast but very comfortable. Easter LR tomorrow.

name: Icy and muddy but still great LR
description: Was going to run on some packed ice trail but it was 45 degrees so the ice was real melty. Good ankle strengthening but miles 2-4 were 6:50-7:00. Aside from those miles it was 6:16 avg inc the last mile in a fast but easy 5:50. Overall really great run, didn't feel nearly as gassed at the end as I have the last 2 weeks. 75m week check.

name: Last day here - Anchorage sucks
description: Ran through some shitty parts of Anchorage, really windy today in like every direction. Some drunk homeless guy almost threw a bottle at me. Ready to get back to the better parts of the US.

name: Evening Run
description: Was hard. Super snowy, kinda sore from multiple plane trips and no sleep. Wout tomorrow

name: WU
description: Neato

name: Broken 8s
description: Felt good. Not crazy fast (2s in 29-30) but felt real easy.

name: CD
description: Yup. Burner again

name: Nice day but felt kinda iffy
description: It was OK

name: Jeff again
description: Left achilles was hurting a lot at the start, glad I didn't stop because it got to feeling way better by the end and it's just feeling better in general now. Light wout tomorrow, big one on Monday.

name: Cold and icy workout at Porter
description: 3 up 2 wout 4 down. Ks were 32, 31, 29. Lots of ice on the track, kinda slippery. Hope its nicer on Monday.

name: 10 ez
description: Was pretty good after all. Kimda cold and its snowing again, ran the last few under 7 nice and easy.

name: Workout day
description: Burner up, burner down, workout was just over 3. 6x4 in 64, 7th in 66 so I cut to 2x2 in 31. Really tough, didn't feel great even at the start, so pretty happy with it overall. Considering also that it was cold and kind of windy, running 4:00 or under in these conditions would bode really well for the rest of the season. We'll see Thursday.

name: Short arb w/ boys
description: Easy short arb, didn't feel great but it was humid and its my first real run in a week. 40mpw is gonna be real easy

name: Hot and humid
description: Kinda hard. F

name: ABR
description: Yeah. Was good. Is good.

name: Rainy, was going to go more
description: Was super hot and humid earlier and started raining, so just ran in that. Dark and a lot of lightning, so I finished early.

name: 6 in the jungle
description: Getting dark out and had just rained, so the natty lands were super green and humid, felt like a jungle. Got some pretty crazy pics on the run too.

name: Late run back home
description: Packing and in the car all day. P sore.

name: Fell ouch
description: There are new pot holes that weren't here before and it was dark. Left leg is a little beat up for the race tomorrow. Lmao

name: WU
description: Knee is felling a bit better. Wont be too much competition in this one.

name: Essence of Freedom 5k
description:
Champ. Mapped it out and it was 3.24 miles. Also as an award I got a free pair of shoes from Fleet Feet which is dope. Some lady sent me this pic lol. 

Race was dank, it was just me and my friend Spak the whole time, dropped him halfway and beat him by about a minute, probably about 5 flat pace on the second half. Paced by a bunch of old vets on motorcycles blasting Led Zeppelin and some lady standing up on one holding a huge flag. Crossed the line and got a water bottle from a fat old man wearing an NRA hat. Also the post-race snacks were just hot dogs. Dankest race ever fo sho.

name: CD
description: Yeet

name: Slow Bill can get even slower
description: Aerobically felt real easy, legs felt pretty tired between my bruised knee and the race yesterday. 65 degrees out felt super nice. Also Ricardo (Berto) yelled my name from a car.

name: 99% humidity
description: Super humid out, literally 99%. Aerobically felt fine, legs felt better, but obviously was super sweaty. Trying to run during the day tomorrow, should be a nice change of pace.

name: Nice to run during the day
description: Sun was set by the time I was done. Also we have a shit ton of really good left over fried chicken, so had a bunch of that. Will be eating chicken for the next several days. I will not want to eat fried chicken ever again by the end of this.

name: Cold LR
description: High of 65 today, but it was sunny so super nice. Wish every day of the summer could be like this. Easiest feeling run of the week so far. Pretty soon this will be the shortest run I do lol. Also probably need to keep it a little slower.

name: Getting slower...
description: Felt nice n' easy, worked from 7:15 down to 6:50. Also ran the last 800 in 2:30 to get a feel for 8k GP since no w/outs this week. That felt easy too.

name: Windy day
description: Felt like I was running into the wind the whole time. Felt alright, a little tightness but nothing too bad.

name: Run
description: ran

name: Best run yet
description:
Drove over to the DPRT and did a loop down the trail and back up through Mount Prospect and Wheeling. 65 and sunny so perfect running weather, except for the windStarted off kinda slow, some of the middle miles were probably 6:20s. Only did that because it was a long run, slow Bill will be back in force tomorrow. 

Also have been doing abs at least every other day.

name: Ran into some DFDC boys
description: Ran into Humlauf and a current runner. Slowed down to like 7:30 with them for a bit. Fun to hear some current team gossip and remember back to my hs days. Time to watch some D1 races, 1500 semis on now.

name: EZ downhill
description: Minus the downhill cause it's the prairie state. Ran through Del-Mar woods (satanist place) and stepped in some turd. Nice.

name: 6.9 miles in 69 degrees
description: Planned on only running 6. I'm so deep in the memes that I even do it accidentally.

name: WU
description: This will suck. F.

name: Milk Mile championship heat
description: Felt way easier than last year, wasn't even aerobically tired when I finished. Got like 6th or 7th to last in a heat with mostly current and future D1 guys so that was pretty sweet. Crispy played Club TT over the speakers which was a good pump up. If I ever do this again I think I can at least go under 6 but this was still a PR lol.

name: Easy run thru Lincolnshire
description: Asked my Dad where I should run and he said "Go west, young man!" so that's what I did. It's been a nice easy week but that was probably the easiest feeling run of all. 63 on the week, going for 70 next week.

name: Run to Old School
description: Felt easy, p humid out tho. Dad picked me up at Old School to go on a bike ride up the DPRT.

name: DPRT w Dad
description: Felt easy. Nice

name: Humid day
description: Felt pretty good and wound up running a little fast. 86% humidity was not great, hope that drops soon.

name: Hotter but dryer
description: Through Riverwoods, kinda buggy and 80 degs but only 45% humidity so felt nice. Decent run, feeling a bit of pain in my left heel but I have before and it's never been a big problem. Will watch out though and stick to soft surfaces.

name: Kinda sore

name: LR with the boys
description: On the DPRT by Maine South. Felt pretty good, hamstrings started hurting after a while but nothing too bad. Heel is better after icing it.

name: Cranky Old Bastard
description: Saw an old guy wearing a cycling team shirt with that across the front. Pretty dank. Was hot and humid but actually felt pretty good. Also congrats on the 70 min half Juggz!

name: F
description: Waited till night to run but it was still hellishly hot and humid, made worse by my not expecting it. Also was v dehydrated even though I've been drinking water pretty regularly. Mother Nature can be a colossal bitch sometimes.

name: 70 and sunny indoors
description: At HP rec center. Ran same pace the whole way. Felt pretty good, aside from the expected stiffness from running 120 laps inside. High of 70 tomorrow, gonna fell amazing.

name: US Champs will be sick
description: A little sore as aftermath of indoor run yesterday, some brief knee pain and otherwise typical hamstring pain, need to continue strengthening those young men. Felt good otherwise despite 90% humidity.

name: Pretty neat run
description: Still a little sore from it being my 5th consecutive mileage increase week and the indoor track, but felt much better. Especially not worried since the next 2 weeks are another 75 and then down to a 65. I ahould be feeling super fresh that next week moving into the 80s and above.

name: Resisting the urge to hammer
description: Felt super good, tried to keep it as slow as I could after dropping to 6:20s for a couple middle miles. Also had some unfortunte encounters with bigass puddles.

name: Cold but humid
description: Ran around Northbrook for a while, felt really easy, but I guess it kinda should this early in the summer. USATF is gettin bumpin, just in time for the boys to show up.

name: Des Moines - the T&F capital of the US
description: Nice and easy with Crispy and Aids. Found a pretty nice path, also have never felt this slow because of all the pro runners around.

name: Humid and hilly
description: This is not what I was told Iowa would be like. Felt pretty decent though.

name: Stinky run
description:
Had to poop in the middle or the run and immediately after almost got sprayed by a skunk. Almost got the legendary double stink lol. Route got messed up by flooding. 

Also because of early long run followed by sitting in the stands at USATF and driving for 7 hours had some bad soreness in my IT bands all day, but it felt better on the run and now after. Good run overall, can't wait for dry season.

name: Meteorology is a fake science
description: Hourly weather called for a 35% chance of scattered showers starting 45 mins into my run. It turned out to be a flash flood starting 10 mins into my run. Will only be using weather radar from now on because it's clear I have a better idea how to read a radar map than most meteorologists. Will be running more as soon as this damn rain lets up

name: Got rained on again
description: Brand new set of clothes and shoes, got poured on yet again. Should be dry tomorrow.

name: Nice day and new shoes
description: Wearing some new green and white pegs, felt just a little rough at the start but they should feel perfect tomorrow. Ran slow and easy for most of it, decided to run the last mile comfortably fast, ended up being 5:03 which was quicker than I thought I was going. July 4th 10k is one week from today, planning on racing with the pack for the first lap (no slower than 5:35) and then dropping it the second, hopefully like 5:15s. Based off today that shouldn't be too unreasonable.

name: Run #1
description: Pretty hot out today but still a nice run. There was something else I was gonna write but i forgot it. Lol

name: Run #2
description: Legs were pretty tired after a 5 hour serving shift, good to get this one done though. I am the only person working at the restaurant who was born in the US and doesn't speak with an accent so it's gonna be kind of a trippy rest of summer.
